!! # Morphology
!!
!! INTRODUCTION TO MORPHOLOGICAL ANALYSER OF THE Moksha LANGUAGE.


Multichar_Symbols !!‚Čą!!@CODE@ / Analysis symbols
!!
!! The morphological analyses of wordforms of the Moksha language are presented
!! in this system in terms of following symbols.
!! (It is highly suggested to follow existing standards when adding new tags).
+TY√Ą 	!!= @CODE@ Underdeveloped.



!! The parts-of-speech tags are:
+Ex/N
+Ex/A
+Ex/V

 +A 		!!‚Čą * **@CODE@**:  adjective
 +Adv 		!!‚Čą * **@CODE@**:  adverb
 +CS 		!!‚Čą * **@CODE@**:  subordinating conjunction
 +CC 		!!‚Čą * **@CODE@**:  coordinating conjunction
 +Det		!!‚Čą * **@CODE@**:  Determiner
 +Interj 	!!‚Čą * **@CODE@**:  interjection
 +N 		!!‚Čą * **@CODE@**:  noun
 +Pcle 		!!‚Čą * **@CODE@**:  particle
 +Po 		!!‚Čą * **@CODE@**:  postposition
 +Pron 		!!‚Čą * **@CODE@**:  pronoun
 +Qnt 		!!‚Čą * **@CODE@**:  Quantifier
 +V 		!!‚Čą * **@CODE@**:  verb

 +Descr		!!‚Čą * **@CODE@**:  descriptive
 +MWE		!!‚Čą * **@CODE@**:  Multiword element
!! The parts of speech are further split up into:
!!
!! **Nouns:**
 +Prop 		!!‚Čą * **@CODE@**:  proper
 +CollN 	!!‚Čą * **@CODE@**:  used with paired nouns **collective nouns**
 +Relat 		!!‚Čą * **@CODE@**:  relator nouns, mainly meronyms 
!!
!! **Pronouns:**
 +Dem 		!!‚Čą * **@CODE@**:  demonstrative
 +Indef 	!!‚Čą * **@CODE@**:  indefinite
 +Dep 		!!‚Čą * **@CODE@**:  dependent word requiring the presence of another, e.g. **–ľ–Ķ–Ĺ—Ć**
 +Exclusive	!!‚Čą * **@CODE@**:  —Ā—Ć–ļ–į–ľ–ĺ–Ĺ–∑–į
 +Intensive !!‚Čą * **@CODE@**:  intensive pronoun
 +Interr 	!!‚Čą * **@CODE@**:  interrogative
 +PerifMod	!!‚Čą * **@CODE@**:  periferal modifier —Ā—Ć–ļ–į–ľ–ĺ–Ĺ–∑–į, –ļ–į–≤–ĺ–Ĺ–Ķ—Ā—ā
 +Pers 		!!‚Čą * **@CODE@**:  personal
 +Recipr 	!!‚Čą * **@CODE@**:  reciprocal
 +Recip 	!!‚Čą * **@CODE@**:  reciprocal
 +Refl 		!!‚Čą * **@CODE@**:  reflexive
 +Rel 		!!‚Čą * **@CODE@**:  relative
!!
!! personal pronouns use additional tags:
!! ```
 +Sg1 +Sg2 +Sg3 +Pl1 +Pl2 +Pl3 !!= @CODE@
!! ```
!!
!! Adverbs:
 +Adv-Ideoph 	!!= * **@CODE@: These are ideophonic descriptors used to modify the verb**: 
            	!!           *–≤—č—Ä–ļ –Ľ–ł–≤—ā—Ź—Ā—Ć*  "**flit** and it flew off"
 +Deg 	     !!= * ;@CODE@: This is degree, depricate + AdA
 +Manner     !!= * **@CODE@**:  with reference to type of adverb
 +Spat 	     !!= * **@CODE@**:  spatial
 +Temp 	     !!= * **@CODE@**:  temporal
 +Emphatic   !!= * **@CODE@**:  used with negation particles –į—Ą–ł, 
 +EvidNfh    !!‚Čą * **@CODE@**:  –ļ–Ľ–Ķ

! Postpositions
! __+Spat__, __+Temp__
!!
!! Interjections:
 +Formulaic  !!= * **@CODE@**:  greetings,
